Title: Object: A mosque with an antique fragment in Old Alexandria near the Gate of Rosetta
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 19 in volume I: two men standing at the entrance of a mosque with an antique column, a man carrying a load on his shoulder in the right foreground, a man talking to a couple who sit on the ground on the left; after Mayer. 1801-1803 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.I.19)
